content.description:
Start on a good jug/pinch and make a long move to a decent lip hold.  Using a cool left toehook gain the sloping lip then a good jug.  Finish straight up on sharp limestone. 

  Head east to downclimb.  careful not to kick rocks down when walking to the downclimb.
content.protection: several pads.  The landing is a bit irregular.

content.description:
Start compressed on a roof feature with a good left heel hook.  Core up and pop for a jug pinch at the lip.  Finish up good holds to a sharp top out.  The low angle rock below the horizontal crack is off for feet. 

  Head east and down climb.  Careful not to kick any rocks down when walking to the descent.
content.protection: A few pads and a spotter feels better.

content.description:
A fantastic roof on the south side of the canyon with good rock and great climbs. 

  There is more room for establishment here.
